sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / kubectl
    participant API as K8s API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Operator as Training Operator Controller<br/>opendatahub namespace
    participant Pods as Worker Pods<br/>User namespace
    participant Svc as Headless Service<br/>(pod DNS discovery)
    participant Prom as OpenShift Monitoring<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over User,Operator: Flow 1: Training Job Lifecycle
        User->>API: 1. Create PyTorchJob CR<br/>Auth: User credentials
        API->>Webhook: 2. Validation webhook callback<br/>HTTPS/9443, TLS (self-signed)
        Webhook-->>API: Admission Response (allow/deny)
        API-->>User: CR created
        Operator->>API: 3. Watch detects new CR<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
        Operator->>API: 4. Create Worker Pods<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
        API-->>Operator: Pods created
        Operator->>API: 5. Create Headless Services<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
        API-->>Operator: Services created
        Pods->>Svc: 6. DNS lookup for peer discovery<br/>Framework port/TCP, No encryption
        Pods->>Pods: 7. Training data exchange<br/>Framework port/TCP, No encryption
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 230)
        Note over User,Pods: Flow 2: MPI Job Execution
        Operator->>API: 1. Create ConfigMap (hostfile),<br/>RBAC (SA, Role, RoleBinding)<br/>HTTPS/443
        Operator->>API: 2. Create Worker Pods<br/>HTTPS/443
        Operator->>API: 3. Create Launcher Pod<br/>(with kubectl init container)<br/>HTTPS/443
        Note over Pods: Launcher runs mpirun
        Pods->>API: 4. kubectl exec to workers<br/>HTTPS/443, Launcher SA token
        Pods->>Pods: 5. MPI execution on workers<br/>via kubectl exec stream<br/>TLS 1.2+, SA RBAC
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 240)
        Note over User,Pods: Flow 3: PyTorch Elastic Training
        Operator->>API: 1. Create HPA for elastic scaling<br/>HTTPS/443
        Pods->>Pods: 2. Worker rendezvous at Master<br/>29500/TCP c10d, No encryption
        Note over API: HPA controller scales workers
        API->>Operator: 3. HPA triggers scale event
        Operator->>API: 4. Reconcile pods (add/remove)<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    end

    rect rgb(245, 245, 255)
        Note over Prom,Operator: Metrics Collection
        Prom->>Operator: Scrape /metrics<br/>HTTP/8080, No auth<br/>PodMonitor, NetworkPolicy allows
    end
